        "class": "",
        "text": "—See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 10:36-37",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Hebron is midway between Jerusalem and Beersheba, and twenty miles from either. The first name of the city, which is one of the most ancient in the world (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 13:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), was Mamre (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 13:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), from the name of its chief (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 14:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). It is now called El-Khulîl (“the friend”), from Abraham. It was a city of refuge (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 21:11-13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). If the view taken as to the chronology of this chapter is correct, this assault is identical with those touched upon in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 11:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 14:6-15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
